<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF8014463A5F7D5972B8A97" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF8014463A5F7D5972B8A97" blockId="26.[151,760,2005,2060]" lastBlockId="26.[828,1437,190,437]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463A5F7D592688CCE" bold="true" box="[151,281,2005,2028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF801446213F7D592BB8CCE" author="JACOBY M." box="[289,458,2005,2028]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="229 - 243" part="9" refId="ref31246" refString="JACOBY M. 1887 b: Descriptions of some new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera contained in the Leyden museum. Notes from the Leyden Museum 9: 229 - 243." title="Descriptions of some new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera contained in the Leyden museum" type="journal article" year="1887" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1887b)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from two females and with some doubts classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014461AAF7F59181832E" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1864" box="[664,752,2037,2060]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Doridea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014461AAF7F59181832E" box="[664,752,2037,2060]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Doridea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequent authors catalogued it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014467FBF0BE963B8BF7" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1864" box="[1225,1354,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014467FBF0BE963B8BF7" box="[1225,1354,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Platyxantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF801446668F0BE90058BD7" author="WEISE J." editor="SCHENKLING S." firstAuthor="WEISE" journalOrPublisher="Berlin" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref33576" refString="WEISE J. 1924: Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. W. Junk, Berlin, pp. 1 - 225." title="Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus" year="1924">WEISE 1924</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF80144604FF0DE977D8BD7" author="WILCOX J. A." box="[893,1036,222,245]" editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX 1973</bibRefCitation>
) and most recently 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014467EEF0DE962B8BD7" author="REID C. A. M." box="[1244,1370,222,245]" firstAuthor="REID" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Entomology" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 9" part="38" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." title="Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1999">REID (1999)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF801446081F0FE975B8A37" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[947,1066,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF801446081F0FE975B8A37" box="[947,1066,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I examined the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF8014467EEF0FE965E8A37" box="[1244,1327,254,277]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntype</typeStatus>
deposited in the RMNH, and a photograph of the second female deposited in the MCZ, and in my opinion both 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF80144660DF13E96ED8A77" box="[1343,1436,318,341]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntypes</typeStatus>
are females of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014460D0F15E970D8A57" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1894" box="[994,1148,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudoscelida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014460D0F15E970D8A57" box="[994,1148,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Pseudoscelida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on general habitus. However, this placement is tentative and should be confirmed by male specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
